<TEXT>
one of the abductors of scott heimdal the 
american gold miner who was kidnapped in ecuadors jungle on april 
28 and freed after 61 days in captivity has been arrested police 
said wednesday 
they identified him as a member of a colombian guerrilla group 
who lived in neighboring ecuador and said he was tied in with a 
colombian drug trafficker who was freed from prison by a guerrilla 
attack 
the police communique said according to our investigations 
the kidnappers of scott heimdal are roberto andres moreno and his 
brother ruben dario who are members of the peoples liberation 
army and luis pablo tobar a drug trafficker freed from the prison 
of tena 
in his hometown of peoria ill heimdal said he had no way of 
knowing if those arrested were responsible for his kidnapping and 
questioned whether they would ever be found 
those names mean nothing to me heimdal said in a telephone 
interview wednesday night i suppose its possible but not very 
the jungles a very very big place the only way i would know if 
it were them is if i saw a photograph 
heimdal said the name of the group that kidnapped him is the 
popular liberation army not the peoples liberation army named in 
the police report 
the police report said the brothers are from ecuador and that 
tobar is colombian only roberto andres moreno has been arrested 
the report said it gave his brothers name only as ruben dario 
the peoples liberation army operates along the colombiaecuador 
border on the western edge of the amazon rain forest 
the communique gave no details of the arrest 
it said however that roberto moreno had kept in contact with 
tobar when tobar was imprisoned in tena a village in ecuadors 
eastern jungle 
colombian guerrillas attacked the prison in august 1988 and 
freed tobar and other four colombian drug traffickers according to 
officials reports two police officers were killed 
heimdals captors asked for ransom money to press their fight 
against the colombian government 
heimdal 28 was released june 29 after his family paid a ransom 
of 60000 most of the money came from donations from his hometown 
heimdals parents came to ecuador to secure his release 
following secret negotiations they all left quito for peoria on 
july 2 
last april 28 a band of men wearing camouflage uniforms and 
carrying assault rifles seized heimdal when he was in a canoe 
heimdal was traveling on the bermeja river the kidnapping took 
place in the jungle about five miles from the colombian border and 
100 miles northeast of quito 
heimdal had been working with iminco a gold mining company 
since october he operated electronic equipment to locate gold 
deposits on the river bottom and also oversaw construction of a 
large dredge 
