<TEXT>
the soviet armed forces may be leaving 
hungary but it seems some of their weapons are staying behind 
there have been persistent reports of illegal traffic in 
firearms from a district of the capital that is home to a russian 
base the magyar hirlap newspaper reported tuesday 
it said it had learned that a heavy machine gun that can be 
mounted on an armored vehicle sells for 1500 and a machine gun 
can be had for between 50 and 410 bullets usually cost just over 
a penny apiece 
the newspaper quoting police sources said that in one incident 
a red army soldier reported having been approached last month by a 
hungarian man and a woman who said they wanted to buy his ak47 
assault rifle 
soviet military authorities alerted hungarian police who found 
out that the wouldbe buyers were a hungarian bricklayer and a 
prostitute the two were detained and then released since they 
could not be charged with any crime the newspaper said 
the paper quoted local precinct police chief capt arpad szabadi 
as saying two hungarian soldiers were caught recently with duffel 
bags filled with automatic pistol parts that they said they bought 
from soviet soldiers 
</TEXT>
