<TEXT>
a nasa researcher analyzing 30000 images 
taken a decade ago by the voyager ii space probe discovered a 
hidden moon in saturns outermost ring 
it was actually in the first image i looked at said mark 
showalter a scientist at nasas ames research center in mountain 
view it was exactly where i expected it to be 
showalter on july 2 found a bright 12milediameter orb 
undetected by earthbased telescopes 
i remember i was so excited i worked through july fourth he 
said tuesday after the space agency announced the discovery of 
saturns 18th moon 
in 1986 national aeronautics and space administration 
researchers first theorized a moon was hidden within what is known 
as the enckes gap around saturn but showalter said he wasnt able 
to search for it until recently 
the honest truth is we just didnt work on this for a few 
years showalter said when you drop a research project its 
very hard to pick it back up 
his find confirmed what scientists had believed for several 
years that undiscovered moons could be hidden among saturns 
three major icy rings making them undulate and causing gaps in 
several minor rings 
theory has predicted this new moon for years said david 
morrison chief of ames space science division its very 
gratifying to find that the theory was correct its almost a 
textbook example of the scientific process 
showalter 32 found the moon by using a computer program he 
designed to sort through the 30000 saturn images sent back to 
earth by voyager in 1980 and 1981 
the moon saturns smallest orbits in enckes gap within the 
planets outermost major ring 
showalter and ames planetary ring expert jeff cuzzi theorized 
that a small moon was creating a 200mile wide gap with its orbit 
and was leaving a moonlet wake pattern similar to boat wakes 
the computer program was based on that hypothesis 
the trick was writing the computer program to tell me which 
images to look at showalter said after that it was actually a 
days work to find it 
during the next several days he found 11 images of the moon 
pete waller manager of public information for nasa said the 
moon is orbiting about 73600 kilometers from saturns cloud tops 
and weighs about 1 trillion tons its tentatively known as 1981s13 
the discovery was reported last week in a publication by the 
international astronomical union which now must certify the find 
and approve a name that could a year 
showalter has suggested pan the greek god of shepherds because 
the moon creates a socalled shepherding effect by pushing 
material away from its orbit to cause the ring gap 
showalter said he doesnt expect any more hidden moons to be 
found within that gap but scientists have theorized that 
undiscovered moons might be spotted in another major gap around 
saturn known as the cassini division 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

