the president did not seem to know much about souters opinions 
in my view it would have been inappropriate to ask him his 
views on specific issues said bush more important are the 
broad concepts of excellence is the man qualified does he share a 
broad view that what he ought to do on the bench is interpret the 
constitution and not legislate and so thats all i need 
samp along with others trying to get a handle on souter turned 
to the great computerized legal data banks for information the 
nominee has been a federal appeals judge only since april and said 
samp he has had absolutely zero written opinions to date 
but souter also was on the new hampshire supreme court for seven 
years and an associate justice of the state superior court for five 
years before that a 12year paper trail the handy thing about 
judging judges part of their job is explaining their decisions 
we have gotten a printout of all his decisions we are talking 
about 700800 if we include every opinion of the new hampshire 
supreme court issued during the time he was on the bench said 
samp if we are looking at the ones he authored there will be 
100150 
