<TEXT>
britain said today that it plans by the mid1990s 
to withdraw half of the more than 66000 troops it has stationed in 
west germany and to cut the nations overall regular forces by 18 
percent 
defense secretary tom king announcing proposed wideranging 
conventional defense cutbacks to parliament also said the 
government planned to maintain some 40 royal navy warships the 
current ceiling is about 50 
king proposed that the royal air force be cut from 89000 
personnel to 75000 and the army from 160000 to 120000 
britain has 66700 servicemen and women deployed in west 
germany they are the second biggest foreign military presence 
after the united states 
the announcement followed a fivemonth review of defense 
expenditure by prime minister margaret thatcher and a committee of 
top cabinet ministers in the light of a reduced soviet threat 
the government long the most hawkish in nato and one of the 
western alliances highest defense spenders kept news of the 
review secret until word leaked several weeks after it began 
king said britain will make no reductions in its nuclear 
arsenal retaining the present polaris missiles and updating them 
with four new missilecarrying us trident submarines within the 
next few years 
it is a time of opportunity and hope for change yet without 
putting at risk the safe protection of our country king told the 
house of commons our aim is an orderly and planned transition to 
the new world unfolding 
he said britain will discuss the proposed cutbacks with its nato 
allies 
and he said implementation hinged on the signing of an eastwest 
agreement on conventional arms cuts final arrangements for german 
unification and the pace of the withdrawal of soviet troops from 
other east european countries 
king said the proposals would mean reductions in british defense 
expenditure but he gave no details the figures would be announced 
in an autumn treasury statement he added 
in addition king said there will be further immediate cutbacks 
to lop 11 billion off the 386 billion defense budget for this 
fiscal year which ends in march we shall be easing back on army 
recruiting and retiring early several ships and submarines he 
said 
citing higherthanexpected inflation the government announced 
last month the cancellation of orders for 33 tornado jet fighters 
as a major saving on the current budget 
government officials said mrs thatcher discussed the outcome of 
the review last week with service chiefs the cabinet committees 
report was debated and accepted by the full 22member cabinet 
thursday morning 
</TEXT>
