vegas have been barred from defending their 1990 national 
championship in next years ncaa tournament because of recruiting 
violations in 1977 when most of them were about 7 
the ncaa sanction writes an end to a painful episode in 
college sports a story that spans a decade of great change and 
vigorous debate one would like to think that the rules violations 
committed by unlv coach jerry tarkanian 13 years ago are less 
likely today but who can be sure 
in fairness to the national collegiate athletic association the 
long delay in this case is largely the fault of tarkanian after 
establishing his rules violations the ncaa tried to suspend him 
from coaching for two years tarkanian sued in federal court to 
block the action and in 1988 won in the us supreme court 
the court ruled that the ncaa contract with member schools 
empowered it to punish the schools but only the schools had power 
to reprimand the coaches they employ it took 11 years to get that 
far 
fairness also means apportioning some blame to unlv which 
should have punished tarkanian should have done so years before 
he got to the supreme court but demurred to that extent the 
university is the cause of its own current troubles 
nevertheless ncaa sanctions this late in the game smack of 
revenge if tarkanian is out of reach then the ncaa will punish 
him by penalizing his players and his school which of course 
stands to lose millions in tournament profits 
were all for high ncaa standards and vigorous enforcement but 
by 1990 the unlv case had become a loser and should have been 
written off to experience 
