<TEXT>
the fourth announced us nuclear weapons 
test of the year was detonated wednesday deep beneath the surface 
of the nevada test site 
the energy department said the test which was not announced in 
advance was uneventful and was an apparent success 
we had no problems with it doe spokesman jim boyer said 
the weapon was listed as having a yield of less than 20 
kilotons and boyer said it was in the smaller range of the 
underground detonations at the nations nuclear proving grounds 
the warhead was detonated at 8 am 1300 feet beneath the 
surface of ranier mesa the site was about 90 miles northwest of 
las vegas 
the test was the 703rd conducted at the site since weapons 
testing began there in 1951 and was the 498th test since the 
limited test ban treaty was signed in 1963 
last year 12 warheads were detonated there 
</TEXT>
