<TEXT>
the bush administration named a veteran 
aerospace executive wednesday to head an independent committee that 
will review nasas plans for the future of the nations space 
program 
the committee under chairman norman r augustine will report 
its findings in four months its mandate is to look into all phases 
of the space program and make recommendations for alternate 
approaches when appropriate 
augustine has been chairman and chief executive officer of the 
martin marietta corp which builds the titan series of rockets 
among its many spacerelated activities 
augustine was the only appointee named in an announcement by 
vice president dan quayle who is head of the national space 
council the announcement said augustine was recommended by richard 
h truly the administrator of national aeronautics and space 
administration 
the committee was formed because of a behindthescenes struggle 
between nasa and the national space council over control of the 
space program quayle and the council have sought to persuade nasa 
to seek alternate approaches to a number of major projects 
including president bushs plan to establish a manned base on the 
moon and send an expedition to mars 
nothing is off the table this is a toptobottom review of 
the space program said a source from the vice presidents side 
who asked not to be identified 
the announcement however sought to make clear that truly was 
not relinquishing his responsibility to run the space agency 
reports in washington were that truly had threatened to resign if 
another authority was imposed on him 
truly is a former astronaut who was brought back from the navy 
to run the manned space program after the fatal challenger accident 
in january 1986 
the committee will operate as an independent entity reporting 
to the administrator of nasa and will submit its findings to the 
administrator of nasa and with the administrator to the vice 
president it said 
the committee is to review the future of the civil space 
program including both management issues and program content 
its members according to the announcement will review 
appropriateness of planned activities organizational balance and 
structure adequacy of skills balance between roles of government 
and the private sector possible contributions by other government 
agencies the need to maintain a strong research and development 
capability and assurance that missions can be carried out 
successfully 
the committee members will be individuals selected for their 
knowledge of space activities and management expertise the 
announcement said 
augustines career includes both private and government posts 
including under secretary of the army he received the 
distinguished service medal the highest civilian decoration of the 
defense department four times 
</TEXT>
