<TEXT>
iraq and kuwait have never agreed on the demarcation of their 
border since kuwait gained its independence from britain in 1961 
shortly after kuwait gained its independendence iraq claimed 
sovereignty and the kuwaitis asked britain for assistance britain 
sent in paratroopers and they were replaced by an arab force led by 
egypt which acted as a buffer between the two countries until 
tensions eased in 1963 
iraq reportedly has sent thousands of troops to its 
100milelong southern border with kuwait although iraq has denied 
building up troops along the border 
here is a brief chronology at the events of this dispute 
july 17 iraqi president saddam hussein accuses kuwait and the 
united arab emirates of flooding the oil market and driving prices 
down and that the move cost iraq 14 billion in lost oil revenue 
he further charges that arab states in the persian gulf of 
conspiring with the united states and israel to weaken iraqs 
economy and undermine its military buildup 
july 18 iraq acccuses kuwait of stealing 24 billion worth of 
oil from wells along the disputed border with iraq and of seeking 
to wreck the countrys economy by overproducing oil and thus 
pushing down prices 
july 19 kuwait cancels a state of alert it declared in an oil 
dispute with iraq 
july 20 kuwaiti officials and diplomats suggest iraqs sudden 
outburst of belligerence is aimed at getting its creditors 
including kuwait to write off billions of dollars in debts from 
the 19801988 iraniraq war 
july 24 the us defense department announces that us navy 
warships and aircraft were holding a shortnotice exercise in 
the persian gulf with the united arab emirates about 600 miles 
south of the kuwaitiraq dispute 
july 24 kuwait reinstates a state of alert it declared july 16 
and canceled after three days of tension between the two 
oilproducing countries 
july 25 the iraqi government in baghdad said that it will not 
be intimidated by us pressure in its oil dispute with neighboring 
kuwait and saddam summoned the us ambassador for talks 
president hosni mubarak of egypt says iraq and kuwait plan to meet 
in saudi arabia this weekend in an effort to resolve their dispute 
</TEXT>
