rising rate of aids among teens up by 35 percent between january 
1989 and may 1990 from 342 cases to 530 
he also noted that onefifth of all people with aids are in 
their 20s about 27500 people because the average time from 
infection with the aids virus until onset of the disease is 
believed to be nine years many of these people probably were 
infected during their teens 
