lesia outside chikurubi maximum security prison near harare 
questioned him in downtown harare and then saw he was driven to 
the main airport and put aboard a johannesburgbound flight without 
a passport or travel documents 
he was not allowed to speak with reporters 
lesia was arrested in may 1987 under sweeping emergency powers 
that allowed for indefinite detention without trial 
he was accused of importing a boobytrapped tv set into zimbabwe 
from mozambique earlier in 1987 
the set exploded in a harare apartment killing the wife of an 
official of the south african guerrilla organization the african 
national congress 
