home affairs minister moven mahachi said lesia was the only 
detainee held in zimbabwe without trial 
mahachi cited reforms in south africa easing of regional 
tensions and political harmony at home as reasons for ending the 
emergency at midnight wednesday 
the white minority government of former rhodesian prime minister 
ian smith introduced the state of emergency in 1965 to crack down 
on black nationalists now in power 
since rhodesia became blackgoverned zimbabwe in 1980 the 
emergency has been renewed every six months by a parliamentary vote 
