the labor department said wednesday it could 
find no evidence of a leak of unemployment statistics earlier this 
month 
the departments investigation was triggered by a report that 
about a minute and a half before release of the june figures by its 
bureau of labor statistics on july 6 one trader sold bond futures 
heavily on the chicago board of trade 
we looked into it we have no evidence that there was a 
leak said spokesman bob zachariasiewicz 
the department gives its monthly unemployment data to news 
organizations at 8 am on condition that it not be made public 
until 830 am this practice called an embargo gives reporters a 
chance to digest the material before they must write their stories 
some other departments such as commerce and agriculture 
release sensitive economic statistics to reporters in a locked room 
and then let them out all at the same time a lockup release 
