yesterday was a very good example of just how well the 
circuitbreaker functions leo melamed chairman of the chicago 
mercantile exchange said tuesday 
the dow drop helped cause a similar decline in the stockindex 
futures market where traders bet on the direction of stock prices 
by buying and selling contracts based on market indexes 
the price tumble tripped circuitbreakers on the chicago 
merc and the chicago board of trade prompting brief trading halts 
that are designed as safeguards against a market crash 
merc officials through an automated conference call stayed in 
touch with the other future exchanges on monday as they have done 
in previous market drops an official said before the hearing 
merc president william j brodsky said officials had several 
conversations with new york stock exchange president richard grasso 
brodsky said the chicago exchanges also were in touch with 
federal regulators at the commodity futures trading commission 
which in turn passed along pertinent information to the securities 
and exchange commission which oversees the stock market 
yesterday was about as normal as you can expect for something 
thats not normal said brodsky 
the circuit breakers were put in place to forestall a collapse 
like that of oct 19 1987 when the dow jones plummeted more than 
500 points 
the dow average of 30 industrial stocks the most widely watched 
measure of the stock markets activity dropped more than 100 
points early monday before regaining about half the loss to close 
down 56 points 
the new york stock exchange has asked its member firms for 
voluntary compliance with a proposed temporary ban on computerized 
selling tactics when the market rises or falls 50 points 
