<DOCNO> AP900725-0224 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
eastern airlines and several of its top managers 
were indicted today on criminal charges of falsifying aircraft 
maintenance records and other aircraftsafety documents 
the 60count indictment alleges a fraudulent scheme to try to 
minimize flight delays and cancellations that resulted in flights 
by improperly maintained or repaired airplanes 
the violations allegedly took place from july 1985 to october 
1989 at john f kennedy international and laguardia airports in new 
york hartsfield international airport in atlanta and eastern 
headquarters in miami 
attorney general dick thornburgh said in a statement that the 
alleged conspiracy strikes a raw nerve in anyone who has ever 
boarded an airplane 
thousands of innocent passengers may have been put at risk 
every day by the criminal actions of these defendants thornburgh 
said 
eastern faces a maximum fine of 30 million each individual 
defendant faces up to five years in prison and a 250000 fine on 
each count 
the indictment charges that by tampering with log books work 
cards and maintenance records eastern did cause aircraft that 
were not properly maintained or repaired to fly and carry 
unsuspecting passengers 
none of the alleged violations caused any accidents or injuries 
authorities said 
the airline and nine employees were charged with conspiracy 
fraud keeping false records concealing information from the 
federal aviation administration and other charges 
the charges follow a yearlong federal investigation and the 
collapse of plea bargain talks in which eastern refused to admit to 
conspiracy charges 
martin shugrue appointed to run eastern by a bankruptcy judge 
said tuesday the airline was prepared to admit to fraudulent 
maintenance and recordkeeping but not conspiracy 
andrew j maloney the us attorney in brooklyn said the 
charges involved critical items including radar landing gear 
automatic pilot instruments and fuel systems 
the indictment alleges eastern and several managers used 
intimidation and coercion to force the airlines maintenance 
personnel to avoid and minimize flight delays and cancellations 
it accuses eastern and the workers of falsifying aircraft 
maintenance records to make it fraudulently appear that scheduled 
maintenance and corrective repairs had been completed 
in addition to the airline named in the indictment were edward 
upton easterns staff vice president of maintenance and 
engineering during the period thomas lewis easterns northern 
area director of maintenance and seven other maintenance 
supervisors and foremen 
a criminal indictment is unprecedented in the airline industry 
and could add to easterns woes as it seeks to regain passengers 
build service and reorganize under federal bankruptcy protection 
after a bitter strike 
i think the public will recognize these are historical events 
that dont bear on eastern today said shugrue who has run the 
airline for about three months 
shugrue said eastern has undergone and passed a rigorous 
